        "content": "<p>rahulchaphalkar opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13886\">PR #13886</a> from <code>rahulchaphalkar:fix-ci-wasi-nn</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>changed <code>panic!</code> to <code>bail!</code> in <code>download()</code> and <code>.lock().unwrap()</code> to <code>.lock().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())</code> in wasi-nn backends. This isolates error caused by a DNS failure in one thread, and not allow it to poison other threads running other tests, <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/actions/runs/29350702096/job/87145948188#step:8:368\">example</a>.</li>\n<li>Added retries to <code>download()</code> to in an attempt to resolve intermittent network issues reaching the server, <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/actions/runs/29350702096/job/87145948188#step:8:328\">example</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>(This is a draft PR for now, want to see whats happening with CI failures in Windows <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/actions/runs/29340495721/job/87110767184#step:8:295\">like here</a> with <code>illegal instruction</code>)<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
